happy...  But, majority of the time I get numerous random tells even when I am on Roleplay; &quot;I died in such and such zone, can you xp rez me&quot;...-or- &quot;I died at blah and need xp rez&quot;.  Quite a few of them being while I am auctioning, or just plain busy, I get many of those where the body is 3+ zones away... and I don't want to take the tread mill trip to said zone to rez so and so...<br><br>I've already asked a few higher level clerics, between 50-60; and most of them say they do not charge for xp rezes...<br><br>Which makes me feel bad sometimes when I ask for 60-100pp to do an xp rez...*Currently have lvl 39 rez* and then there are other clerics who are shouting &quot;k bring bodies to blah area, xp rezing for free&quot;... <br><br>However, a majority of the time, I get told I will be paid 100pp *upon the rez*, then I only get about 10-20pp for doing the rez at all and the response &quot;oh sorry didn't have 60-100pp on me&quot;, which sometimes I think is false... Or I rez the person and am only paid 10-20pp...  Hmm that's about the price of a GG or TL somewhere, oh wait, gets me closer to the &quot;I died in such and such zone, can you xp rez me&quot; person.<br><br>It's not like every druid or wizard do GGs and TLs for free... and if they are, the ones' I've found are far and inbetween... *not turning to a druid &amp; wizzie flame*.... So, with that said, should I just not charge at all for xp rez or what?  And if I do charge what should it be? <p><p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://members.aol.com/reinehass/sig1.jpg" p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E6FA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/umelandia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Melandia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Knight<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><