 60 (no, not a case of me not wanting to rezz people, this is from the attitudes I've gotten from people when I said I said I couldn't/wouldn't come rezz them).  I've actually been called an asshole (more than once, and not the only name I've been called) because I didn't want to rezz someone (yeah, corpse was one zone over, but I was headed to have fun with my guild).  Granted, 99% of the time when I'm offered cash for rezzes I decline.  Lately though I've been taking cash offered, especially if the person offering is 50+, mainly due to the fact that Luclin is a serious drain on a clerics bank account due to the lack of vendor drops, unless yer hunting in like FG, but most of my groups have been in ME, Umbral, Ahkeva or Grey, so I've taken cash offered for rezzes to fund symbols, not through some desire to be rich. heh.<br><br>Anywho, back to the main subject.  If I were to run around /ooc'ing rezzing for pp. It'd probably depend on the avg level of the zone.  I mean, OT, 10 - 20pp. EW, 30pp, any 50+ zone 50pp (shrug)<br><br>!Calric <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E6FA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/upaluwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paluwen </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Defender<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#4B0082>(1/4/02 7:36:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=170.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: To Rez... or not to Rez...</span><hr size=1> First off i agree the res issue is way screwed up, seems to me that i never even asked for a res before i hit level 35ish, around a gozillion years ago. Now people ask for a res to regain lvl 15, to the point they ooc for it for an hour.<br><br>second point is that clerics are your be