l/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  begging ect will not only usualy not get you that res but will not help you to get others.  <br><br>   Straying back on the topic now.  I am 58th lvl, non epic cleric.  I would say a good 95% of the time I will not even accept donations (we all have our greedy days), I believe in &quot;Karma&quot;, call me foolish but it seems to work.  I Res as much as I can without hurting my group which is about as fair as I can be. I still run around KC and offer to res, I still stop by a corpse with gear on it and do the /who all and see if they need a res.  I like to help as much as possible.  This is me and only me and might not be my thinking on that day you ask me (remember the 5% of the time, mabey its not your day, hell you died so seems like you should understand things are going down hill for ya anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  <br><br>   A few pointers to GET that res you so greatly want.  If we are in the same zone work to get your corpse to me, if you are half way around the world and I am in the zone you died in do what you can in assisting me to get to your corpse (loc's are GREAT for this).  If I am not in the same zone try to get me a gate there if it's anydistance at all.  Remember I am a cleric and although I have Jboots they are not that fast and not everyone has them so the runs are not only long at times but dangerous, hell you got killed there so dont think I can walk in and play god alone I am a healer not good at soloing espicialy when it's to res someone else.  An aranged GG and escort will almost always get me to say yes (*NOTE the GG MUST include a ride back, or close to where I was, I am not always bound where I left from so leaving me in some god forsaken place where you parished will not endear me to you)<br><br>   These are simple tips to help everyone, they are from my point of view and mine alone, but I will bet you will also help in dealing with other clerics.<br><br>   As far as charging for a res, I personaly dont, that's just me.  It's totaly right to charge for them as I see it (NOT for groupmates, that's just sick).  Think about it, lightening someone's pocket everytime they die will mabey encurage them to play a bit safer next time.<br><br>   Just remember this being a multiplayer game you will almost always need help sometime or another yourself. That being said I have had good luck in the past getting GG's almost always with no problem, I have also had no problem getting my carcas dragged out of some really crappy places by your friendly monk/rogue and occasional brave warrior or the like that I had res'd in the past and they never charged me to get my body.  Just food for thought.<br><br>Lakeland<br>58th lvl Cleric<br>Sabretooth Bear Clan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E6FA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/upaluwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paluwen </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Defender<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#4B0082>(1/4/02 5:58:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=170.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: To Rez... or not to Rez...</span><hr size=1> im writing all the cleric replyers names down to /tell for res in the future...hehe they all said they never charge<br><br>wait, they've all already ressed me before...crap what do ya do when every cleric on the server has ressed you at some point?<br><br>sidenote: Did Korn sound like she never dies at all to anyone else? Can i get that secret? I seem to avg about 1-2 times a day <p></p><i></i></td></tr>